<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_bwar"
    xml:lang="os">
    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bwar</orth></form>
    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bawær</orth></form>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>тело</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>body</q>
        </cit></sense>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>jæ bwar ægasæj dær rafasta</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>все его тело покрылось сыпью</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>his whole body broke out in hives</q>
            </cit>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>jæ bwar ægasæj dær rafasta</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>все его тело покрылось сыпью</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>his whole body broke out in hives</q>
            </cit>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru"><bibl><author>Вс. Миллер</author></bibl> возводит к <mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*upa-vara-</w></mentioned> от <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>var-</w><gloss><q>tegere</q></gloss></mentioned>; в этом случае исходное
        значение было бы ‘покров’, ‘оболочка’; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>varṇa-</w><gloss><q>вид</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>внешность</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>форма</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><w>varman-</w><gloss><q>покров</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>кора</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>панцирь</q></gloss></mentioned>, , в особенности же <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>varah-</w><gloss><q>грудь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>uras-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>var</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>bar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"
                    ><lang/><w>goar</w><gloss><q>грудь</q></gloss></mentioned>. С звуковой стороны
        этимология приемлема: %iup%i → %ib%i, как в %ibа%i из <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>upa</w></mentioned>, -%ibæl%i из <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>upari</w></mentioned>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæstæ"/> из
            <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>upasta-</w></mentioned> . Развитие значения
        ‘оболочка’ — ‘тело’ также находится в пределах допустимого, в особенности если учесть
        значение ‘грудь’ в других иранских языках. — Иранское <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>tanu-</w><gloss><q>тело</q></gloss></mentioned> получило в осетинском
        значение ‘нижняя часть живота’ (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæn"/>).%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 155</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en"><bibl><author>Ws. Miller</author></bibl> traces the word back to <mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*upa-vara-</w></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>var-</w><gloss><q>tegere</q></gloss></mentioned>; in this case the
        initial meaning should have been ‘cover’, ‘shell’; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>varṇa-</w><gloss><q>sight</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>appearance</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>form</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><w>varman-</w><gloss><q>cover</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>bark</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>armature</q></gloss></mentioned>, , in particular <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>varah-</w><gloss><q>chest</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>uras-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>var</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>bar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"
                    ><lang/><w>goar</w><gloss><q>chest</q></gloss></mentioned>. As for the phonetic
        part, the etymology is acceptable: %iup%i → %ib%i, like in %ibа%i which is from <mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>upa</w></mentioned>, -%ibæl%i from <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>upari</w></mentioned>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæstæ"/> from
            <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>upasta-</w></mentioned>. The development of the
        meaning 'shell' — ‘body’ is also within reasonable, in particular if we count the meaning
        'meaning' in other Iranian languages. — Iranian <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>tanu-</w><gloss><q>body</q></gloss></mentioned> got the meaning ‘bottom
        part of the stomach’ in Ossetic (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæn"/>).%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 155</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
